#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn40.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Moggallānavagga "
msgstr "1. By Moggallāna "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn40.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Sakkasutta "
msgstr "10. With Sakka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.270, sc1
msgctxt "sn40.10:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—jetavane antarahito devesu tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi. "
msgstr "And then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from Jeta’s Grove and reappeared among the gods of the Thirty-Three. "

msgctxt "sn40.10:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sakko devānamindo pañcahi devatāsatehi saddhiṃ yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, with five hundred deities came up to Mahāmoggallāna, bowed, and stood to one side. Mahāmoggallāna said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: buddhasaraṇagamanaṃ → buddhaṃ saraṇagamanaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn40.10:2.1"
msgid "“Sādhu kho, devānaminda, buddhasaraṇagamanaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "“Lord of gods, it’s good to go for refuge to the Buddha. "

#. VAR: Buddhasaraṇagamanahetu → buddhaṃ saraṇagamanahetu (bj)
msgctxt "sn40.10:2.2"
msgid "Buddhasaraṇagamanahetu kho, devānaminda, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti. "
msgstr "It’s the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "sn40.10:2.3"
msgid "Sādhu kho, devānaminda, dhammasaraṇagamanaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "It’s good to go for refuge to the teaching. "

msgctxt "sn40.10:2.4"
